In [16]:
# Group data by showroom_regency and get unique showroom_names in each regency
showroom_regency_names = df.groupby('showroom_name')['showroom_regency'].unique()

# Create a dataframe to store the relationship between showroom_regency and showroom_name
regency_name_df = pd.DataFrame({'Showroom Regency': showroom_regency_names.index, 'Showroom Names': showroom_regency_names.values})

# Create an Excel writer
output_path = 'showroom_regency.xlsx'
with pd.ExcelWriter(output_path) as writer:
    regency_name_df.to_excel(writer, sheet_name='Regency-Name Relationship', index=False)

print(f"Data has been saved to {output_path}")

Data has been saved to showroom_regency.xlsx

price_stats = df.groupby('id_merk')['price_cash'].describe()

# Print the statistics
print("Descriptive Statistics of Price Based on Car Make:\n")
for make, stats in price_stats.iterrows():
    print(f"Car Make: {make}")
    print(f"Count: {stats['count']}")
    print(f"Mean Price: {stats['mean']:.2f}")
    print(f"Median Price (Q2): {stats['50%']:.2f}")
    print(f"Minimum Price: {stats['min']:.2f}")
    print(f"Maximum Price: {stats['max']:.2f}")
    print("\n")
